In the Top Chess Engine Championship (TCEC) Season 16 Superfinal the top two engines from the Premier Division compete in a 100-game match for the TCEC Grand Champion title. In the case of a drawn match there will be a rapid match of 16 games with a time control of 25' + 10" with random openings selected from earlier in the same Season. In case it is still tied there will be a Blitz match of 8 games with a time control of 3' + 2".

The engines receive 120 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. Official website: tcec-chess.com

Standings and knockout tree here https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/khanty-fide-world-cup-2019/1/55/2
